        <item>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>Helping Expand Lending Practices in Rural Communities Act of 2014 or the HELP Rural Communities Act of 2014 - Amends the Dodd-Frank Wall Street Reform and Consumer Protection Act to direct the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau (CFPB) to establish an application process under which a person who lives or does business in a state may apply to have a county designated as a rural area for purposes of a federal consumer financial law.</p> <p>Prescribes criteria for the CFPB to consider when evaluating such an application. </p> <p>Requires the CFPB to enter each such application into a sortable, downloadable database publicly accessible through its website.</p>]]></text>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2014-01-27T22:14:56Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
          <actionDate>2014-01-14</actionDate>
          <updateDate>2014-01-14T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
        </item>
